South Africa's Food Framwork: More predatory than healing

In October, South Africa's national Department of Health launched its National Food Plan, which was described by long-time activist Mmatshilo Motsei as imposing "more predatory than healing" onto the South African population.

As part of the plan process, Motsei wrote a report and put forward recommendations to protect LGBTQI+ people from the impacts of food insecurity.

The PFMA Bill is an abiding stumbling block. It would leave LGBTQI+ people vulnerable to the same kinds of prejudice and the denial of public benefits that forced marriages and plagiarism rulings are employed against women.
